data.title: Margaret of Anjou
data.meta_description: Profile of queen consort to king henry vi of england Margaret of Anjou featuring biographical facts, historical events and details of Margaret of Anjou's personal life.
data.text:
Profession: Queen Consort to King Henry VI of England

Biography: Figurehead for the Lancastrians during the War of the Roses (1455-85).

Born: March 23, 1430

Birthplace: Pont Ã  Mousson, Duchy of Lorraine, France

Star Sign: Aries

Died: August 25, 1482 (aged 52)

Historical Events

Coronation as Margaret of Anjou as Queen Consort of England at Westminster Abbey

Wars of the Roses: Battle of Towton - Duke Edward of York defeats the Lancastrian army, deposes King Henry VI and Queen Margaret of Anjou and proclaims himself as King Edward IV

Personal Life

Margaret of Anjou weds King Henry VI of England in Titchfield, Hampshire
